# Function/Role

# Responsibility

- Review the PQR results as Marketing Authorization Holder (MAH) or according to specific local responsibility and assess the necessity for further CAPAs, revalidation or amendments to the PQR;
- If applicable, create the PQR of in-country GMP activities (e.g. QC Testing);
- If all manufacturing steps including batch certification are performed by a CMO, involve responsible Regulatory Affairs department to create Annex 6 and/or 10 and attach these annexes to the MAH Review document.

# External Supply Quality Assurance

- Prepare and approve the PQR plan if all manufacturing steps including batch certification are performed by a CMO and/or ESQ;
- Approve the PQR plan of products where CMOs are involved;
- Implement responsibilities for PQR creation in TQAs with external CMOs;
- Request PQR timely to external CMOs;
- If batch certification is done by IMQ, forward CMO PQR to IMQ for review and approval;
- If all manufacturing steps including batch certification are performed by a CMO, review and approve CMO PQR;
- If batch certification is done by ESQ, prepare, review and approve the PQR;
- Notify CQA that approved PQRs are ready for MAH Review;
- When needed, escalate issues related to CMO PQRs.

# Qualified Person for batch certification

- Review the PQRs whenever batch certification is done by GRT QP and evaluate (also if raised by CQA during the MAH review) any need for further CAPAs and/or revalidation;
- Approve the PQRs whenever batch certification is done by GRT QP.
- Notify CQA that approved PQRs are ready for MAH Review.
